oai_dc:dc.dc:title: MIXED CHALCOGEN CARBONYL-COMPOUNDS .3. CONSTRUCTION OF THE NEW UNSATURATED MIXED METAL-CLUSTERS FE2RU2(CO)10(MU-CO)(MU-4-SE)(MU-4-TE) AND FE3RU(CO)10(MU-CO)(MU-4-SE)(MU-4-TE)
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: MATHUR, P
CHAKRABARTY, D
HOSSAIN, MM
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: chemistry
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Addition of Ru(CO)4(C2H4) to Fe2Ru(CO)9(mu-3-Se)(mu-3-Te) and to Fe3(CO)9(mu-3-Se)(mu-3-Te) lead to a clean formation of the new unsaturated mixed metal, mixed chalcogen carbonyl clusters, Fe2Ru2(CO)10(mu-CO)(mu-4-Se)(mu-4-Te) and Fe3Ru)CO)10(mu-4-Se)(mu-4-Te) respectively. The Fe3Ru cluster is also obtainable from the photolysis of a solution containing Fe2Ru(CO)9(mu-3-Se)(mu-3-Te) and Fe(CO)5.
